ipSecFlowMonitorMIB.name: ipSecFlowMonitorMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module proposed to IETF.

Phase-1 group updated with mode config metrics in globals as well as IKE peer table. Phase-2 group updated with new group metrics. New grou failures added to Failure group. Notifications pertaining to new group added. SPI table deprecated and an updated IPsec SA table added. Compliance clauses updated.

Third submission of the draft to IETF. Changes incorporated based on comments received on the second draft. Highlights: 1) IKE Group made optional 2) Provision to accomodate other Phase 1 protocols. 3) Phase 1 Peer Association table decoupled from IKE group. 4) Local and Remote value indices to Phase 1 Pee Association table constrained to 128-bit length by MD5 hashing. 5) Mapping of Phase 2 tunnels to Phase 1 tunnels made generic (non-IKE). 6) Phase 1 traps redefined as `Control Channel' traps. 7) High capacity counters defined for Phase-1 and Phase-2 expired counters.

ipSecFlowMonitorMIB.description: This is a MIB Module for monitoring the structure and status of IPSec-based networks. The MIB has bee designed to be adopted as an IETF standard. Henc vendor-specific features of IPSec protocol are exclude from this MIB. Acronyms The following acronyms are used in this document: IPSec: Secure IP Protocol VPN: Virtual Private Network ISAKMP: Internet Security Association and Key Exchange Protocol IKE: Internet Key Exchange Protocol SA: Security Association MM: Main Mode - the process of setting up a Phase 1 SA to secure the exchanges required to setup Phase 2 SAs QM: Quick Mode - the process of setting up Phase 2 Security Associations using a Phase 1 SA. Phase 1 Tunnel: An ISAKMP SA can be regarded as representing a flow of ISAKMP/IKE traffic. Hence an ISAKMP is referred to as a 'Phase 1 Tunnel' in this document Control Tunnel: Another term for a Phase 1 Tunnel. Phase 2 Tunnel: AN instance of a non-ISAKMP SA bundle in which all the SA share the same proxy identifiers (IDii,IDir) protect the same stream of application traffic. Such an SA bundle is termed a 'Phase 2 Tunnel'. Note that a Phase 2 tunnel may comprise different SA bundles and different number of SA bundles at different times (due to key refresh). Overview of IPsec MIB The MIB contains six major groups of objects which are used to manage the IPSec Protocol. These groups include a Levels Group, a Phase-1 Group, a Phase-2 Group, a History Group, a Failure Group and a TRAP Control Group. The following table illustrates the structure of the IPSec MIB. The Phase 1 group models objects pertaining to IKE negotiations and Phase 1 tunnels. The Phase 2 group models objects pertaining to IPSec data tunnels. The History group is to aid applications that do trending analysis. The Failure group is to enable an operator to do troubleshooting and debugging of the VPN Router. Further, counters are supported to aid detection of potential security violations. In addition to the five major MIB Groups, there are a number of Notifications. The following table illustrates the name and description of the IPSec TRAPs. For a detailed discussion, please refer to the IETF draft draft-ietf-ipsec-flow-monitoring-mib-01.txt.

ipSecGlobalOutCompTooSmallPkts.name: ipSecGlobalOutCompTooSmallPkts

ipSecGlobalProtocolUseFails.name: ipSecGlobalProtocolUseFails

ipSecSpiTable.name: ipSecSpiTable
ipSecSpiTable.description: The IPsec Phase-2 Security Protection Index Table. This table contains an entry for each active and expiring security association.

ipSecSpiEntry.name: ipSecSpiEntry
ipSecSpiEntry.description: Each entry contains the attributes associated with active and expiring IPsec Phase-2 security associations.

ipSecSpiIndex.name: ipSecSpiIndex
ipSecSpiIndex.description: The number of the SPI associated with the Phase-2 Tunnel Table. The value of this index is a number which begins at one and is incremented with each SPI associated with an IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel. The value of this object will wrap at 2,147,483,647.

ipSecGlobalInNewGrpReqs.name: ipSecGlobalInNewGrpReqs
ipSecGlobalInNewGrpReqs.description: The total number of New Group exchanges initiated remotely.

ipSecGlobalOutNewGrpReqs.name: ipSecGlobalOutNewGrpReqs
ipSecGlobalOutNewGrpReqs.description: The total number of New Group exchanges initiated locally.

ipSecGlobalInNewGrpReqsRejected.name: ipSecGlobalInNewGrpReqsRejected
ipSecGlobalInNewGrpReqsRejected.description: The total number of New Group exchanges initiated remotely that ended in a failure.

ipSecGlobalOutNewGrpReqsRejected.name: ipSecGlobalOutNewGrpReqsRejected
ipSecGlobalOutNewGrpReqsRejected.description: The total number of New Group exchanges initiated locally that ended in a failure.

ipSecSaTable.name: ipSecSaTable
ipSecSaTable.description: The IPsec Phase-2 Security Association Table. This table identifies the structure (in terms of component SAs) of each active Phase-2 IPsec tunnel. This table contains an entry for each active and expiring security association and maps each entry in the active Phase-2 tunnel table (ipSecTunTable) into a number of entries in this table. The index of this table reflects the <destination-address, protocol, spi> rule for identifying Security Associations.

ipSecSaEntry.name: ipSecSaEntry
ipSecSaEntry.description: Each entry contains the attributes associated with active and expiring IPsec Phase-2 security associations.

ipSecSaIndex.name: ipSecSaIndex
ipSecSaIndex.description: The index, in the context of the IPsec tunnel ipSecTunIndex, of the security association represented by this table entry. The value of this index is a number which begins at one and is incremented with each SPI associated with an IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel. The value of this object will wrap at 2,147,483,647.

ipSecSaDirection.name: ipSecSaDirection
ipSecSaDirection.description: Phase-2 IPsec security associations are simplex. Hence a particular security association is used either for securing outgoing traffic or decoding incoming traffic. This column identifies the direction of the security association represented by this entry.

ipSecSaValue.name: ipSecSaValue
ipSecSaValue.description: This is the value of the Security Protection Index (SPI) assigned by the system to the security association represented by this entry.

ipSecSaProtocol.name: ipSecSaProtocol
ipSecSaProtocol.description: This column represents the security protocol (AH, ESP or IPComp) for which this security association was setup.

ipSecSaStatus.name: ipSecSaStatus
ipSecSaStatus.description: This column represents the status of the security association represented by this tabel entry. If the status of the SA is 'active', the SA is ready for active use. The status 'expiring' represents any of the various states that the security association transitions through before being purged.

ipSecHistTableSize.name: ipSecHistTableSize
ipSecHistTableSize.description: The window size of the IPsec Phase-1 and Phase-2 History Tables. The IPsec Phase-1 and Phase-2 History Tables are implemented as a sliding window in which only the last n entries are maintained. This object is used specify the number of entries which will be maintained in the IPsec Phase-1 and Phase-2 History Tables. An implementation may choose suitable minimum and maximum values for this element based on the local policy and available resources. If an SNMP SET request specifies a value outside this window for this element, a BAD VALUE may be returned.

ipSecHistCheckPoint.name: ipSecHistCheckPoint
ipSecHistCheckPoint.description: The current state of check point processing. This object will return ready when the agent is ready to create on-demand history entries for active IPsec Tunnels or checkPoint when the agent is currently creating on-demand history entries for active IPsec Tunnels. By setting this value to checkPoint, the agent will create: a) an entry in the IPsec Phase-1 Tunnel History for each active IPsec Phase-1 Tunnel and b) an entry in the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel History Table and an entry in the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel EndPoint History Table for each active IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ikeTunnelHistTable.name: ikeTunnelHistTable
ikeTunnelHistTable.description: The IPsec Phase-1 Internet Key Exchange Tunnel History Table. This table is implemented as a sliding window in which only the last n entries are maintained. The maximum number of entries is specified by the ipSecHistTableSize object.

ikeTunnelHistEntry.name: ikeTunnelHistEntry
ikeTunnelHistEntry.description: Each entry contains the attributes associated with a previously active IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

ikeTunHistIndex.name: ikeTunHistIndex
ikeTunHistIndex.description: The index of the IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel History Table. The value of the index is a number which begins at one and is incremented with each tunnel that ends. The value of this object will wrap at 2,147,483,647.

ikeTunHistTermReason.name: ikeTunHistTermReason
ikeTunHistTermReason.description: The reason the IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel was terminated. Possible reasons include: 1 = other 2 = normal termination 3 = operator request 4 = peer delete request was received 5 = contact with peer was lost 6 = applicationInitiated (eg: L2TP requesting the termination) 7 = failure of extended authentication 8 = local failure occurred. 9 = operator initiated check point request

ikeTunHistActiveIndex.name: ikeTunHistActiveIndex
ikeTunHistActiveIndex.description: The index of the previously active IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

ikeTunHistPeerLocalType.name: ikeTunHistPeerLocalType
ikeTunHistPeerLocalType.description: The type of local peer identity. The local peer may be indentified by: 1. an IP address, or 2. or a fully qualified domain name. 3. or a distinguished name.

ikeTunHistPeerLocalValue.name: ikeTunHistPeerLocalValue
ikeTunHistPeerLocalValue.description: The value of the local peer identity. If the local peer type is an IP Address, then this is the IP Address used to identify the local peer. If the local peer type is id-fqdn, then this is the FQDN of the local entity. If the local peer type is a id-dn, then this is the distinguished named string of the local entity.

ikeTunHistPeerIntIndex.name: ikeTunHistPeerIntIndex
ikeTunHistPeerIntIndex.description: The internal index of the local-remote peer association. This internal index is used to uniquely identify multiple associations between the local and remote peer.

ikeTunHistPeerRemoteType.name: ikeTunHistPeerRemoteType
ikeTunHistPeerRemoteType.description: The type of remote peer identity. The remote peer may be indentified by: 1. an IP address, or 2. or a fully qualified domain name. 3. or a distinguished name.

ikeTunHistPeerRemoteValue.name: ikeTunHistPeerRemoteValue
ikeTunHistPeerRemoteValue.description: The value of the remote peer identity. If the remote peer type is an IP Address, then this is the IP Address used to identify the remote peer. If the remote peer type is id-fqdn, then this is the FQDN of the remote peer. If the remote peer type is a id-dn, then this is the distinguished named string of the remote peer.

ikeTunHistLocalAddr.name: ikeTunHistLocalAddr
ikeTunHistLocalAddr.description: The IP address of the local endpoint for the IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

ikeTunHistLocalName.name: ikeTunHistLocalName
ikeTunHistLocalName.description: The DNS name of the local IP address for the IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel. If the DNS name associated with the local tunnel endpoint is not known, then the value of this object will be a NULL string.

ikeTunHistRemoteAddr.name: ikeTunHistRemoteAddr
ikeTunHistRemoteAddr.description: The IP address of the remote endpoint for the IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

ikeTunHistRemoteName.name: ikeTunHistRemoteName
ikeTunHistRemoteName.description: The DNS name of the remote IP address of IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel. If the DNS name associated with the remote tunnel endpoint is not known, then the value of this object will be a NULL string.

ikeTunHistNegoMode.name: ikeTunHistNegoMode
ikeTunHistNegoMode.description: The negotiation mode of the IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

ikeTunHistDiffHellmanGrp.name: ikeTunHistDiffHellmanGrp
ikeTunHistDiffHellmanGrp.description: The Diffie Hellman Group used in IPsec Phase-1 IKE negotiations.

ikeTunHistEncryptAlgo.name: ikeTunHistEncryptAlgo
ikeTunHistEncryptAlgo.description: The encryption algorithm used in IPsec Phase-1 IKE negotiations.

ikeTunHistHashAlgo.name: ikeTunHistHashAlgo
ikeTunHistHashAlgo.description: The hash algorithm used in IPsec Phase-1 IKE negotiations.

ikeTunHistAuthMethod.name: ikeTunHistAuthMethod
ikeTunHistAuthMethod.description: The authentication method used in IPsec Phase-1 IKE negotiations.

ikeTunHistLifeTime.name: ikeTunHistLifeTime
ikeTunHistLifeTime.description: The negotiated LifeTime of the IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel in seconds.

ikeTunHistStartTime.name: ikeTunHistStartTime
ikeTunHistStartTime.description: The value of sysUpTime in hundredths of seconds when the IPsec Phase-1 IKE tunnel was started.

ikeTunHistActiveTime.name: ikeTunHistActiveTime
ikeTunHistActiveTime.description: The length of time the IPsec Phase-1 IKE tunnel was been active in hundredths of seconds.

ikeTunHistTotalRefreshes.name: ikeTunHistTotalRefreshes
ikeTunHistTotalRefreshes.description: The total number of security associations refreshes performed.

ikeTunHistTotalSas.name: ikeTunHistTotalSas
ikeTunHistTotalSas.description: The total number of security associations used during the life of the IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

ikeTunHistInOctets.name: ikeTunHistInOctets
ikeTunHistInOctets.description: The total number of octets received by this IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

ikeTunHistInPkts.name: ikeTunHistInPkts
ikeTunHistInPkts.description: The total number of packets received by this IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

ikeTunHistInDropPkts.name: ikeTunHistInDropPkts
ikeTunHistInDropPkts.description: The total number of packets dropped by this IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel during receive processing.

ikeTunHistInNotifys.name: ikeTunHistInNotifys
ikeTunHistInNotifys.description: The total number of notifys received by this IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

ikeTunHistInP2Exchgs.name: ikeTunHistInP2Exchgs
ikeTunHistInP2Exchgs.description: The total number of IPsec Phase-2 exchanges received by this IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

ikeTunHistInP2ExchgInvalids.name: ikeTunHistInP2ExchgInvalids
ikeTunHistInP2ExchgInvalids.description: The total number of IPsec Phase-2 exchanges received on this tunnel that were found to contain references to unrecognized security parameters.

ikeTunHistInP2ExchgRejects.name: ikeTunHistInP2ExchgRejects
ikeTunHistInP2ExchgRejects.description: The total number of IPsec Phase-2 exchanges received on this tunnel that were validated but were rejected by the local policy.

ikeTunHistInP2SaDelRequests.name: ikeTunHistInP2SaDelRequests
ikeTunHistInP2SaDelRequests.description: The total number of IPsec Phase-2 security association delete requests received by this IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

ikeTunHistOutOctets.name: ikeTunHistOutOctets
ikeTunHistOutOctets.description: The total number of octets sent by this IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

ikeTunHistOutPkts.name: ikeTunHistOutPkts
ikeTunHistOutPkts.description: The total number of packets sent by this IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

ikeTunHistOutDropPkts.name: ikeTunHistOutDropPkts
ikeTunHistOutDropPkts.description: The total number of packets dropped by this IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel during send processing.

ikeTunHistOutNotifys.name: ikeTunHistOutNotifys
ikeTunHistOutNotifys.description: The total number of notifys sent by this IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

ikeTunHistOutP2Exchgs.name: ikeTunHistOutP2Exchgs
ikeTunHistOutP2Exchgs.description: The total number of IPsec Phase-2 exchanges sent by this IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

ikeTunHistOutP2ExchgInvalids.name: ikeTunHistOutP2ExchgInvalids
ikeTunHistOutP2ExchgInvalids.description: The total number of IPsec Phase-2 exchanges sent on this tunnel that were found by the peer to contain references to security parameters not recognized by the peer.

ikeTunHistOutP2ExchgRejects.name: ikeTunHistOutP2ExchgRejects
ikeTunHistOutP2ExchgRejects.description: The total number of IPsec Phase-2 exchanges sent on this tunnel that were validated by the peer but were rejected by the peer's policy.

ikeTunHistOutP2SaDelRequests.name: ikeTunHistOutP2SaDelRequests
ikeTunHistOutP2SaDelRequests.description: The total number of IPsec Phase-2 security association delete requests sent by this IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

ikeTunHistInNewGrpReqs.name: ikeTunHistInNewGrpReqs
ikeTunHistInNewGrpReqs.description: The total number of New Group exchanges initiated remotely using this IKE tunnel during its lifetime.

ikeTunHistOutNewGrpReqs.name: ikeTunHistOutNewGrpReqs
ikeTunHistOutNewGrpReqs.description: The total number of New Group exchanges initiated locally using this IKE tunnel during its lifetime.

ikeTunHistInNewGrpReqsRejected.name: ikeTunHistInNewGrpReqsRejected
ikeTunHistInNewGrpReqsRejected.description: The total number of New Group exchanges initiated remotely using this IKE tunnel during its lifetime that ended in a failure.

ikeTunHistOutNewGrpReqsRejected.name: ikeTunHistOutNewGrpReqsRejected
ikeTunHistOutNewGrpReqsRejected.description: The total number of New Group exchanges initiated locally using this IKE tunnel during its lifetime that ended in a failure.

ikeTunHistInConfigs.name: ikeTunHistInConfigs
ikeTunHistInConfigs.description: The total number of Mode Configuration settings received (either CFG-REPLY or CFG-SET payloads) by the local entity on the ISAKMP SA represented by this IKE tunnel.

ikeTunHistOutConfigs.name: ikeTunHistOutConfigs
ikeTunHistOutConfigs.description: The total number of Mode Configuration settings dispatched (either CFG-REPLY or CFG-SET payloads) by the local entity on the ISAKMP SA represented by this IKE tunnel.

ikeTunHistInConfigsRejects.name: ikeTunHistInConfigsRejects
ikeTunHistInConfigsRejects.description: The total number of Mode Configuration settings which were received (either CFG-REPLY or CFG-SET payloads) and rejected by this entity using the ISAKMP SA represented by this IKE tunnel.

ikeTunHistOutConfigsRejects.name: ikeTunHistOutConfigsRejects
ikeTunHistOutConfigsRejects.description: The total number of Mode Configuration settings which were dispatched (either CFG-REPLY or CFG-SET payloads) by this entity and were rejected by the peer (client) using the ISAKMP SA represented by this IKE tunnel.

ikeTunHistEncryptKeySize.name: ikeTunHistEncryptKeySize
ikeTunHistEncryptKeySize.description: The size in bits of the key which was negotiated for the IKE tunnel to be used with the algorithm denote by the column 'ikeTunEncryptAlgo'. For DES and 3DES the ke size is respectively 56 and 168. For AES, this will denot the negotiated key size.

ipSecTunnelHistTable.name: ipSecTunnelHistTable
ipSecTunnelHistTable.description: The IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel History Table. This table is implemented as a sliding window in which only the last n entries are maintained. The maximum number of entries is specified by the ipSecHistTableSize object.

ipSecTunnelHistEntry.name: ipSecTunnelHistEntry
ipSecTunnelHistEntry.description: Each entry contains the attributes associated with a previously active IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ipSecTunHistIndex.name: ipSecTunHistIndex
ipSecTunHistIndex.description: The index of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel History Table. The value of the index is a number which begins at one and is incremented with each tunnel that ends. The value of this object will wrap at 2,147,483,647.

ipSecTunHistTermReason.name: ipSecTunHistTermReason
ipSecTunHistTermReason.description: The reason the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel was terminated. Possible reasons include: 1 = other 2 = normal termination 3 = operator request 4 = peer delete request was received 5 = contact with peer was lost 6 = applicationInitiated (eg: L2TP requesting the termination) 7 = failure of extended authentication 8 = local failure occurred 9 = operator initiated check point request

ipSecTunHistActiveIndex.name: ipSecTunHistActiveIndex
ipSecTunHistActiveIndex.description: The index of the previously active IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ipSecTunHistIkeTunnelIndex.name: ipSecTunHistIkeTunnelIndex
ipSecTunHistIkeTunnelIndex.description: The index of the associated IPsec Phase-1 Tunnel (ikeTunIndex in the ikeTunnelTable).

ipSecTunHistLocalAddr.name: ipSecTunHistLocalAddr
ipSecTunHistLocalAddr.description: The IP address of the local endpoint for the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ipSecTunHistRemoteAddr.name: ipSecTunHistRemoteAddr
ipSecTunHistRemoteAddr.description: The IP address of the remote endpoint for the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ipSecTunHistKeyType.name: ipSecTunHistKeyType
ipSecTunHistKeyType.description: The type of key used by the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ipSecTunHistEncapMode.name: ipSecTunHistEncapMode
ipSecTunHistEncapMode.description: The encapsulation mode used by the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ipSecTunHistLifeSize.name: ipSecTunHistLifeSize
ipSecTunHistLifeSize.description: The negotiated LifeSize of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel in kilobytes.

ipSecTunHistLifeTime.name: ipSecTunHistLifeTime
ipSecTunHistLifeTime.description: The negotiated LifeTime of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel in seconds.

ipSecTunHistStartTime.name: ipSecTunHistStartTime
ipSecTunHistStartTime.description: The value of sysUpTime in hundredths of seconds when the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel was started.

ipSecTunHistActiveTime.name: ipSecTunHistActiveTime
ipSecTunHistActiveTime.description: The length of time the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel has been active in hundredths of seconds.

ipSecTunHistTotalRefreshes.name: ipSecTunHistTotalRefreshes
ipSecTunHistTotalRefreshes.description: The total number of security association refreshes performed.

ipSecTunHistTotalSas.name: ipSecTunHistTotalSas
ipSecTunHistTotalSas.description: The total number of security associations used during the life of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ipSecTunHistInSaDiffHellmanGrp.name: ipSecTunHistInSaDiffHellmanGrp
ipSecTunHistInSaDiffHellmanGrp.description: The Diffie Hellman Group used by the inbound security association of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ipSecTunHistInSaEncryptAlgo.name: ipSecTunHistInSaEncryptAlgo
ipSecTunHistInSaEncryptAlgo.description: The encryption algorithm used by the inbound security association of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ipSecTunHistInSaAhAuthAlgo.name: ipSecTunHistInSaAhAuthAlgo
ipSecTunHistInSaAhAuthAlgo.description: The authentication algorithm used by the inbound authentication header (AH) security association of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ipSecTunHistInSaEspAuthAlgo.name: ipSecTunHistInSaEspAuthAlgo
ipSecTunHistInSaEspAuthAlgo.description: The authentication algorithm used by the inbound encapsulation security protocol (ESP) security association of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ipSecTunHistInSaDecompAlgo.name: ipSecTunHistInSaDecompAlgo
ipSecTunHistInSaDecompAlgo.description: The decompression algorithm used by the inbound security association of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ipSecTunHistOutSaDiffHellmanGrp.name: ipSecTunHistOutSaDiffHellmanGrp
ipSecTunHistOutSaDiffHellmanGrp.description: The Diffie Hellman Group used by the outbound security association of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ipSecTunHistOutSaEncryptAlgo.name: ipSecTunHistOutSaEncryptAlgo
ipSecTunHistOutSaEncryptAlgo.description: The encryption algorithm used by the outbound security association of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ipSecTunHistOutSaAhAuthAlgo.name: ipSecTunHistOutSaAhAuthAlgo
ipSecTunHistOutSaAhAuthAlgo.description: The authentication algorithm used by the outbound authentication header (AH) security association of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ipSecTunHistOutSaEspAuthAlgo.name: ipSecTunHistOutSaEspAuthAlgo
ipSecTunHistOutSaEspAuthAlgo.description: The authentication algorithm used by the inbound ecapsulation security protocol (ESP) security association of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ipSecTunHistOutSaCompAlgo.name: ipSecTunHistOutSaCompAlgo
ipSecTunHistOutSaCompAlgo.description: The compression algorithm used by the inbound security association of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ipSecTunHistPmtu.name: ipSecTunHistPmtu
ipSecTunHistPmtu.description: The Path MTU that was determined for this IPsec Phase-2 tunnel.

ipSecTunHistInOctets.name: ipSecTunHistInOctets
ipSecTunHistInOctets.description: The total number of octets received by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel. This value is accumulated BEFORE determining whether or not the packet should be decompressed. See also ipSecTunInOctWraps for the number of times this counter has wrapped.

ipSecTunHistHcInOctets.name: ipSecTunHistHcInOctets
ipSecTunHistHcInOctets.description: A high capacity count of the total number of octets received by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel. This value is accumulated BEFORE determining whether or not the packet should be decompressed.

ipSecTunHistInOctWraps.name: ipSecTunHistInOctWraps
ipSecTunHistInOctWraps.description: The number of times the octets received counter (ipSecTunInOctets) has wrapped.

ipSecTunHistInDecompOctets.name: ipSecTunHistInDecompOctets
ipSecTunHistInDecompOctets.description: The total number of decompressed octets received by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel. This value is accumulated AFTER the packet is decompressed. If compression is not being used, this value will match the value of ipSecTunInOctets. See also ipSecTunInDecompOctWraps for the number of times this counter has wrapped.

ipSecTunHistHcInDecompOctets.name: ipSecTunHistHcInDecompOctets
ipSecTunHistHcInDecompOctets.description: A high capacity count of the total number of decompressed octets received by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel. This value is accumulated AFTER the packet is decompressed. If compression is not being used, this value will match the value of ipSecTunHcInOctets.

ipSecTunHistInDecompOctWraps.name: ipSecTunHistInDecompOctWraps
ipSecTunHistInDecompOctWraps.description: The number of times the decompressed octets received counter (ipSecTunInDecompOctets) has wrapped.

ipSecTunHistInPkts.name: ipSecTunHistInPkts
ipSecTunHistInPkts.description: The total number of packets received by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ipSecTunHistInDropPkts.name: ipSecTunHistInDropPkts
ipSecTunHistInDropPkts.description: The total number of packets dropped during receive processing by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel. This count does NOT include packets dropped due to Anti-Replay processing.

ipSecTunHistInReplayDropPkts.name: ipSecTunHistInReplayDropPkts
ipSecTunHistInReplayDropPkts.description: The total number of packets dropped during receive processing due to Anti-Replay processing by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ipSecTunHistInAuths.name: ipSecTunHistInAuths
ipSecTunHistInAuths.description: The total number of inbound authentication's performed by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ipSecTunHistInAuthFails.name: ipSecTunHistInAuthFails
ipSecTunHistInAuthFails.description: The total number of inbound authentication's which ended in failure by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel .

ipSecTunHistInDecrypts.name: ipSecTunHistInDecrypts
ipSecTunHistInDecrypts.description: The total number of inbound decryption's performed by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ipSecTunHistInDecryptFails.name: ipSecTunHistInDecryptFails
ipSecTunHistInDecryptFails.description: The total number of inbound decryption's which ended in failure by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ipSecTunHistOutOctets.name: ipSecTunHistOutOctets
ipSecTunHistOutOctets.description: The total number of octets sent by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel. This value is accumulated AFTER determining whether or not the packet should be compressed. See also ipSecTunOutOctWraps for the number of times this counter has wrapped.

ipSecTunHistHcOutOctets.name: ipSecTunHistHcOutOctets
ipSecTunHistHcOutOctets.description: A high capacity count of the total number of octets sent by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel. This value is accumulated AFTER determining whether or not the packet should be compressed.

ipSecTunHistOutOctWraps.name: ipSecTunHistOutOctWraps
ipSecTunHistOutOctWraps.description: The number of times the octets sent counter (ipSecTunOutOctets) has wrapped.

ipSecTunHistOutUncompOctets.name: ipSecTunHistOutUncompOctets
ipSecTunHistOutUncompOctets.description: The total number of uncompressed octets sent by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel. This value is accumulated BEFORE the packet is compressed. If compression is not being used, this value will match the value of ipSecTunOutOctets. See also ipSecTunOutDecompOctWraps for the number of times this counter has wrapped.

ipSecTunHistHcOutUncompOctets.name: ipSecTunHistHcOutUncompOctets
ipSecTunHistHcOutUncompOctets.description: A high capacity count of the total number of uncompressed octets sent by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel. This value is accumulated BEFORE the packet is compressed. If compression is not being used, this value will match the value of ipSecTunHcOutOctets.

ipSecTunHistOutUncompOctWraps.name: ipSecTunHistOutUncompOctWraps
ipSecTunHistOutUncompOctWraps.description: The number of times the uncompressed octets sent counter (ipSecTunOutUncompOctets) has wrapped.

ipSecTunHistOutPkts.name: ipSecTunHistOutPkts
ipSecTunHistOutPkts.description: The total number of packets sent by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ipSecTunHistOutDropPkts.name: ipSecTunHistOutDropPkts
ipSecTunHistOutDropPkts.description: The total number of packets dropped during send processing by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ipSecTunHistOutAuths.name: ipSecTunHistOutAuths
ipSecTunHistOutAuths.description: The total number of outbound authentication's performed by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ipSecTunHistOutAuthFails.name: ipSecTunHistOutAuthFails
ipSecTunHistOutAuthFails.description: The total number of outbound authentication's which ended in failure by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ipSecTunHistOutEncrypts.name: ipSecTunHistOutEncrypts
ipSecTunHistOutEncrypts.description: The total number of outbound encryption's performed by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ipSecTunHistOutEncryptFails.name: ipSecTunHistOutEncryptFails
ipSecTunHistOutEncryptFails.description: The total number of outbound encryption's which ended in failure by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ipSecTunHistOutCompressedPkts.name: ipSecTunHistOutCompressedPkts
ipSecTunHistOutCompressedPkts.description: The total number of outbound packets which were successfully compressed.

ipSecTunHistOutCompSkippedPkts.name: ipSecTunHistOutCompSkippedPkts
ipSecTunHistOutCompSkippedPkts.description: The total number of outbound packets that were to be compressed but which were skipped due to the compression hysteresis.

ipSecTunHistOutCompFailPkts.name: ipSecTunHistOutCompFailPkts
ipSecTunHistOutCompFailPkts.description: The total number of outbound packets that failed compression because they grew in size after compression.

ipSecTunHistOutCompTooSmallPkts.name: ipSecTunHistOutCompTooSmallPkts
ipSecTunHistOutCompTooSmallPkts.description: The total number of outbound packets that were to be compressed but were smaller than the compression threshold size.

ipSecTunHistControlProtocol.description: Identifies the protocol that was used to setup and administer Phase-2 IPsec tunnel. If IKE was used to setup this tunnel, then this value of this column would be `cp-ike'.
